<Document>
<name>Coral Coast — Perth to Kalbarri</name>
<description><![CDATA[<h2>Coral Coast — Perth to Kalbarri</h2><p><i>Western Australia · Indian Ocean Drive / Brand Highway, Perth to Kalbarri</i></p><p><b>580 km from Perth to the Murchison River — Pinnacles desert, pink lakes, white beaches against red gorges.</b></p><table style='font-family:sans-serif'><tr><td><b>Approx. length:</b></td><td>520 km (323 mi)</td></tr><tr><td><b>Drive time:</b></td><td>1–2 days minimum</td></tr><tr><td><b>Best season:</b></td><td>April–October (wildflower season Aug–Oct is the showstopper); summer (Dec–Feb) is hot</td></tr><tr><td><b>Watch out for:</b></td><td>Long empty sections, kangaroos at dawn/dusk, road trains, fierce sun, occasional cyclones in summer</td></tr><tr><td><b>Track points:</b></td><td>579</td></tr></table><hr><p>WA's central west coast is a different country from the southwest — semi-arid scrub, rust-red headlands, and Indian Ocean water that turns electric turquoise on a clear day. The Pinnacles in Nambung National Park are 30,000-year-old limestone columns rising from yellow desert sand. Hutt Lagoon's pink color (strongest from October to early summer) comes from beta-carotene-producing algae. Kalbarri sits on the mouth of the Murchison River where the river has cut a 400 m deep gorge through Tumblagooda sandstone containing some of the oldest fossil tracks of land animals on Earth (around 420 million years). In wildflower season (August–October) the roadside verges turn into a quilt of everlastings, banksias, and kangaroo paws — the world's most diverse temperate flora is here.</p><h3>Scenic points marked on this route:</h3><ul><li><b>The Pinnacles</b> — Thousands of limestone columns to 3.5 m tall in yellow sand — formed 25,000–30,000 years ago when leached calcium re-cemented around plant roots. Drive the 4 km loop or walk the trail at sunset.</li><li><b>Cervantes / Lake Thetis stromatolites</b> — Tiny lake just off the highway with living stromatolites — biofilm-built rocks made by cyanobacteria, the same life form that made Earth's atmosphere oxygen-bearing 3.5 billion years ago.</li><li><b>Geraldton / HMAS Sydney memorial</b> — Hilltop memorial to the 645 men lost when HMAS Sydney was sunk by the German raider Kormoran in November 1941 — Australia's worst naval disaster. The dome is built from 645 stainless-steel seagulls.</li><li><b>Hutt Lagoon</b> — 10 km × 2 km lagoon coloured by Dunaliella salina algae — peak pink intensity is October to early summer, mid-morning to early afternoon. Drive the gravel loop on the western side.</li><li><b>Kalbarri</b> — Fishing village at the mouth of the Murchison. Pelicans fed daily on the foreshore at 8:45 AM. Whale sharks sometimes show offshore in winter; humpbacks pass May–November.</li><li><b>Nature's Window</b> — Wind-eroded sandstone arch framing the Murchison River gorge — the iconic Kalbarri photograph. 1 km return walk; do at sunrise to avoid the heat. Skywalk cantilever platforms 2 km further on.</li></ul><hr><p><i>Track geometry is interpolated between named waypoints — use a routing service to snap to actual road for navigation. Waypoints, scenic POIs, and notes are reliable.</i></p>]]></description>
